Record breaking, history making, goal setting. 50 years of the “Vorsprung durch Technik” claim shaped Audi’s quattro technology and Rally history. The Audi quattro (1980) brought the quattro technology to the tarmac. Then, the Audi Sport quattro S1 Pikes Peak (1987) broke world records. Now, Audi has its sights set on the future: the 2022 Dakar Rally where Audi will be competing with a fully electric drivetrain. • • • •

Trendsetting engine design. For 50 years, the “Vorsprung durch Technik” claim has meant pushing the boundaries of progressive engineering. Making history, the Audi A8 with the Audi Space Frame (1994) defied expectations with its fully aluminium construction. It built on advances from the past, like the lightweight engine design of the Audi 80 B1 (1972), and inspired future models, like the Audi A2 (1999), the first 3L car with 4 doors. Progress is a mindset. • • • •
